    <title>Tomato and Chorizo Soup</title>
		<comment>The reader should remember that seasonal produce will make the best soups. More often than not, local produce is better than foreign alternatives, particularly with short season vegetables. I had the misfortune to try Peruvian asparagus in the middle of September last year, and it is not a product I will endorse here. Nearly every recipe here will require vegetable oil, salt and pepper, so they are omitted from the ingredients list. I recommend Maldon salt, which is widely available, and to my mind is one of the best salts in the world. 
		</comment> 
		<cook>15 min</cook>
		<prep>5 min</prep>
		<price>Â£5</price>
		<veg>No</veg>		
		<width>1440</width>
		<height>900</height>
	</documentinfo>
	<defaults>
		<backgroundcolor>#FFFFFF</backgroundcolor>
		<font>Helvetica Neue Thin</font>
		<fontsize>24</fontsize>
		<linecolor>#000000</linecolor>
		<fontcolor>#000000</fontcolor>
		<fillcolor>#CCCCCC</fillcolor>
	</defaults>
	<ingredients>
		<ingredient name="onion" amount="1" units="whole" />
		<ingredient name="carrot" amount="1" units="whole" />
		<ingredient name="garlic" amount="1" units="whole" />
		<ingredient name="tomato puree" amount="1" units="tbsp" />
		<ingredient name="chopped tomatoes" amount="1" units="tin" />
		<ingredient name="sugar" amount="1" units="tsp" />
		<ingredient name="white chicken stock" amount="300" units="ml" />
		<ingredient name="whole milk" amount="100" units="ml" />
		<ingredient name="chorizo" amount="250" units="g" />
		<ingredient name="fresh thyme" amount="2" units="sprigs" />
	</ingredients>

	<slide id="0" duration="20" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1400" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Tomato and Chorizo Soup</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="15" ystart="70" xend="1400" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
        		<textstring>The spicy, garlicky Spanish sausage lends its flavour to this soup. Although this soup would work fantastically with a fillet of cod or hake, it is delicious by itself as well.

Please click 'Next' or press the right arrow key to begin.</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="950" ystart="15" xend="1400" yend="600" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="20" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false" >
        		<textstring>Please refer to the 'Stocks' slideshow for essential basics  </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_0.png" xstart="250" ystart="260" width="900" height="600" layer="1" />	
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/slideBackground.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />			
	</slide>

	<slide id="1" duration="30" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Step One</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="15" ystart="70" xend="1400" yend="200" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false" >
        		<textstring>Heat a little oil in a pan over a medium heat, and add the peeled and diced onion. Season with salt, and cook until softened but not coloured.  </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text> 
		<text xstart="950" ystart="15" xend="1400" yend="600" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="20" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false" branch="7">
        		<textstring>How to chop an onion...  </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text> 
		<text xstart="100" ystart="550" xend="530" yend="470" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Peel and finely dice the carrot and garlic. Add to the pan with the thyme, then continue to cook for 5 minutes.</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>     		
        		
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_1.png" xstart="100" ystart="150" width="550" height="366" layer="2" />	
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_2.png" xstart="750" ystart="150" width="550" height="366" layer="2" />		
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_3.png" xstart="550" ystart="525" width="550" height="366" layer="2" />		
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/slideBackground.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
		<audio urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/tom_churro_audio_1.mp3" starttime="5" loop="false" />
	</slide>

	<slide id="2" duration="30" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Step Two</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="15" ystart="70" xend="1400" yend="600" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Heat a frying pan over medium high heat. Peel the chorizo of its papery casing, then cut two thirds of it into 1cm thick rounds. Cook these in a small amount of oil in the frying pan for 5-6 minutes, turning frequently to avoid burning.  </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>     
		<text xstart="15" ystart="700" xend="1000" yend="800" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
				<textstring>Add the entire contents of the pan to the vegetable mixture (including any fat which has come out of the chorizo).</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>		
        		
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_4.png" xstart="15" ystart="200" width="700" height="466" layer="2" />	
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_5.png" xstart="725" ystart="200" width="700" height="466" layer="2" />			
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/slideBackground.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
		<audio urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/tom_churro_audio_2.mp3" starttime="5" loop="false" />
	</slide>

	<slide id="3" duration="30" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Step Three</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="15" ystart="100" xend="650" yend="400" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" >
			<textbody >
        		<textstring>Cook this mixture for 2 minutes over a medium heat, mixing to combine. Add the tomato puree and cook for a further 3-4 minutes, until the raw taste from the puree has gone away. </textstring>
      			</textbody>
        </text>
        <text xstart="700" ystart="550" xend="1400" yend="400" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" >
			<textbody >
        		<textstring>Now add the chopped tomatoes and the chicken stock, as well as the sugar. Turn the heat to low, and simmer uncovered.  </textstring>
      			</textbody>
        </text>
        
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_6.png" xstart="700" ystart="70" width="650" height="433" layer="3" />
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_7.png" xstart="15" ystart="360" width="650" height="433" layer="3" />
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/slideBackground.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
		<audio urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/tom_churro_audio_3.mp3" starttime="5" loop="false" />
					
	</slide>

	<slide id="4" duration="30" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Step Four</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="670" ystart="100" xend="1400" yend="400" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
        		<textstring>After 15-20 minutes, check a piece of chorizo. It should be tender and easy to break apart, if not return the pan to the heat for another 10 minutes.</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>  
		<text xstart="670" ystart="700" xend="1300" yend="1000" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Once the chorizo is tender, blend the soup with the best equipment available to you and pass through a fine sieve. Discard the solids.</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>     		
        		
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_8.png" xstart="100" ystart="100" width="550" height="366" layer="2" />	
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_9.png" xstart="700" ystart="250" width="650" height="433" layer="2" />		
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_10.png" xstart="100" ystart="500" width="550" height="366" layer="2" />		
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/slideBackground.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
		<audio urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/tom_churro_audio_4.mp3" starttime="5" loop="false" />
	</slide>
	
	<slide id="5" duration="30" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Step Five</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		
		<text xstart="10" ystart="70" xend="1400" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0">
			<textbody >
        		<textstring>Finely chop the remaining chorizo, and fry in a little oil over a high heat until crispy but not burnt. The rendered fat in the pan should be a beautiful red colour.</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="10" ystart="650" xend="725" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0">
			<textbody >
        		<textstring>Add the milk to the soup, and carefully heat, frothing with a hand blender for a cappuccino like texture. </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>	
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_11.png" xstart="15" ystart="150" width="700" height="466" layer="2" />	
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_12.png" xstart="725" ystart="250" width="700" height="466" layer="2" />		
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/slideBackground.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
		<audio urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/tom_churro_audio_5.mp3" starttime="5" loop="false" />
	</slide>

	<slide id="6" duration="30" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Eat.</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="300" ystart="720" xend="1050" yend="1000" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0">
			<textbody >
        		<textstring>Pour into bowls, and garnish with the crispy chorizo pieces, as well as a little of the rendered fat.</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/IMG_butnut_13.png" xstart="250" ystart="100" width="900" height="600" layer="7" />				
		<image urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/slideBackground.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
		<audio urlname="Tomato and Chorizo Soup/tom_churro_audio_6.mp3" starttime="5" loop="false" />
	</slide>
	
